{
  "texts": [
    "This category covers ocean-related climate resilience issues-such as sea-level rise, coastal erosion, and marine ecosystem degradation-with 46 papers identified under this topic (representing 11% of the reviewed literature).",
    "AI application in coastal and marine AI enhances coastal and marine resilience through predictive analytics, remote sensing, decision support systems, and ecosystem monitoring.",
    "AI models forecast sea-level changes, storm surges, and precipitation patterns, supporting proactive adaptation (Cheye et al., 2024; Ian et al., 2023).",
    "Advanced neural networks, such as BALSSA and D-BALSSA, improve storm surge prediction accuracy, enabling timely disaster warnings (Ayinde et al., 2024; Ian et al., 2023).",
    "AI processes satellite and drone data to monitor coastal ecosystems, mangrove coverage, and coral reef health (Yang et al., 2022b; Maina et al., 2021; Mayamanikandan et al., 2024)."
  ]
}